The paper discusses probabilistic techniques for data analysis and introduces composable generative population models (CGPMs) as a computational abstraction that extends directed graphical models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the integration of CGPMs into BayesDB, a probabilistic programming platform, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of statistics (cs.ST) and systems and control (cs.SY).
